Heat oven to 325 degrees F. Line 13x9-inch pan with foil, with ends of foil extending over sides. Mix crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of pan. Beat cream cheese, sugar, flour and vanilla with mixer until well blended. Add sour cream; mix well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each just until blended. Pour over crust. Bake 40 min. or until center is almost set. Cool completely. Refrigerate 4 hours. Top with pie filling. Use foil handles to lift cheesecake from pan before cutting to serve.